Figure 1 shows our modeling algorithm. To simulate biomass growth as a function of time, we divided the entire time period into finite intervals of 0.002 h (Additional file 2: Fig. S1 shows that further decreasing the interval period did not change the simulation results). In each time interval, a simplified sinusoid equation [41] was used to estimate the cell location in a well-mixed PBR:3l=r2-r2cos(2πfrt),\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
